{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb2c253f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s290"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"290"},"text":"§ 290.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of earnings transferred to the Treasury","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The net earnings derived by the United States from Federal reserve banks shall, in the discretion of the Secretary, be used to supplement the gold reserve held against outstanding United States notes, or shall be applied to the reduction of the outstanding bonded indebtedness of the United States under regulations to be prescribed by the Secretary of the Treasury. Should a Federal reserve bank be dissolved or go into liquidation, any surplus remaining, after the payment of all debts, dividend requirements as hereinbefore provided, and the par value of the stock, shall be paid to and become the property of the United States and shall be similarly applied.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb2c2540-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s7/b"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 7(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/258"},"text":"38 Stat. 258","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66/tIII/s3002/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66, title III, § 3002(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/337"},"text":"107 Stat. 337","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb2c2541-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb2c2542-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb2c2543-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of subsec. (b) [formerly second undesignated par.] of section 7 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913","children":[],"tail":". Subsec. (a) and another subsec. (b) [enacted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/5/tIII/s302/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(5) [title III, § 302(2)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–304] of section 7 are classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s289"},"text":"section 289 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Subsec. (c) of section 7 is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s531"},"text":"section 531 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb2c2544-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/66"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–66","children":[],"tail":" inserted section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
